Some of the place names are Danish in origin, e.g. -by in{Newby, Throxenby, {Scalby}means farm. The holm in {Peasholm}means marsh. {Scalby Mills}is so called because there were several mills on{Scalby beck.}
{ Northstead Manor}was once owned by Richard III. The manor house was excavated in 1912 when{Peasholm Park was laid out.
If an M.P. wishes to vacate his seat he must apply for the stewardship of the Chiltern Hundreds or{Northstead {Manor.}
After a cliff fall at{Scalby Ness}in 1916 a collection of Bronze Age items were revealed. These can be found in Hull Museum.
